# Build outputs — generated from src/pack/, never committed.
#
# ANCHORED TO THE REPO ROOT ON PURPOSE. An unanchored `site/` matches a directory named
# `site` at ANY depth — including `src/theme/site/`, the site's palette, typography and
# template override, which git then refuses to add without a word. The build fails later
# and elsewhere (`theme.custom_dir` aborts on a directory that is not there), so the
# leading slash is what keeps the cause anywhere near the symptom. `site` here means the
# `site_dir` in mkdocs.yml, and only that.
/site/
/dist/
*.pdf

